# Project Tech Stack
- Frontend: React Native (Expo SDK ~57, Expo Router, typed routes, react compiler enabled)
- Language: TypeScript (strict)
- Styling: StyleSheet.create + theme tokens in src/constants/theme.ts (Colors, Fonts, Spacing, BorderRadius). No NativeWind/Tailwind — not installed, don't use it.
- Backend/Database: Supabase (@supabase/supabase-js), session persisted via AsyncStorage

# Rules & Guidelines
- Always use TypeScript with strict type checking.
- Use functional components and hooks.
- Style with StyleSheet.create and the theme tokens in src/constants/theme.ts; support light/dark via useColorScheme.
- Write clean, modular, and reusable code.
- Ensure cross-platform compatibility (iOS, Android, and Web).
- Path aliases: @/* -> src/*, @/assets/* -> assets/*.
- UI copy is in Korean — keep new user-facing strings in Korean unless told otherwise.
- Auth: src/app/_layout.tsx gates routes via Stack.Protected based on session from useAuth() (src/contexts/auth-context.tsx). New authenticated screens go under src/app/(app)/; public screens go alongside login.tsx at src/app/.
- Domain: ChurchPosition (직분: brother/sister/deacon/deaconess/elder) and MemberRole (역할/permission: newcomerTeam/cellLeader/teacher/finance/minister) are distinct — don't conflate them (src/types/member.ts).
- supabase/migrations/ is hand-run SQL (no migration CLI). Add new numbered migration files rather than editing past ones.
